namespace CS2Radar
{
    public class Program
    {
        private static readonly HttpClient client = new HttpClient();

        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("CS2 Radar Starting... (Educational Version)");

            // In a real implementation, we would read the game memory.
            // For educational purposes, we simulate data.
            while (true)
            {
                try
                {
                    // Simulate player data
                    var players = SimulatePlayerData();

                    // Send data to the web server
                    SendDataToServer(players);

                    // Wait before next read
                    Thread.Sleep(100);
                }
                catch (Exception ex)
                {
                    Console.WriteLine($"Error: {ex.Message}");
                }
            }
        }

        static List<Player> SimulatePlayerData()
        {
            var players = new List<Player>();
            var random = new Random();

            // Simulate 10 players
            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)
            {
                players.Add(new Player
                {
                    Id = i,
                    Name = $"Player{i}",
                    Position = new Vector3
                    {
                        X = random.Next(-1000, 1000),
                        Y = random.Next(-1000, 1000),
                        Z = random.Next(0, 100)
                    },
                    Health = random.Next(0, 100),
                    Team = i % 2 == 0 ? 2 : 3 // 2 for CT, 3 for T
                });
            }

            return players;
        }

        static async void SendDataToServer(List<Player> players)
        {
            var data = new { players };
            string json = JsonConvert.SerializeObject(data);
            var content = new StringContent(json, System.Text.Encoding.UTF8, "application/json");

            try
            {
                await client.PostAsync("http://localhost:3000/update", content);
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                Console.WriteLine($"Failed to send data: {ex.Message}");
            }
        }
    }

    public class Player
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public string Name { get; set; }
        public Vector3 Position { get; set; }
        public int Health { get; set; }
        public int Team { get; set; }
    }

    public class Vector3
    {
        public float X { get; set; }
        public float Y { get; set; }
        public float Z { get; set; }
    }
}

1. Advanced Memory Reader with Vector Logic Chaining

cpp
// advanced_memory_vector.h
#pragma once
#include <windows.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <atomic>
#include <thread>

class VectorChainMemoryReader {
private:
    std::atomic<bool> m_running{false};
    HANDLE m_process_handle;
    DWORD m_process_id;
    
    // Vector chain components
    struct MemoryVector {
        uintptr_t base_address;
        std::vector<uintptr_t> offsets;
        size_t data_size;
        std::string vector_name;
    };
    
    std::vector<MemoryVector> m_vector_chains;
    
    // Enhanced pattern for CS2
    struct GameOffsets {
        uintptr_t local_player;
        uintptr_t entity_list;
        uintptr_t view_matrix;
        uintptr_t bone_matrix;
        uintptr_t radar_info;
    } m_offsets;
    
public:
    VectorChainMemoryReader();
    ~VectorChainMemoryReader();
    
    bool Initialize();
    void StartReading();
    void StopReading();
    
private:
    bool FindProcess(const std::string& process_name);
    bool InitializeVectorChains();
    uintptr_t FollowVectorChain(const MemoryVector& chain);
    void ReadingThread();
    
    // Enhanced memory reading with error correction
    template<typename T>
    bool ReadMemory(uintptr_t address, T& value) {
        SIZE_T bytes_read;
        return ReadProcessMemory(m_process_handle, (LPCVOID)address, &value, sizeof(T), &bytes_read) 
               && bytes_read == sizeof(T);
    }
    
    // Vector-based entity reading
    struct PlayerEntity {
        Vector3 position;
        Vector3 view_angles;
        Vector3 velocity;
        int health;
        int team;
        bool dormant;
        std::string name;
        uint32_t weapon_id;
        int armor;
        bool spotted;
        bool defusing;
        bool planting;
        float flash_duration;
    };
    
    std::vector<PlayerEntity> ReadPlayerEntities();
    void UpdateRadarData(const std::vector<PlayerEntity>& entities);
};
cpp
// advanced_memory_vector.cpp
#include "advanced_memory_vector.h"
#include <TlHelp32.h>
#include <iostream>

VectorChainMemoryReader::VectorChainMemoryReader() 
    : m_process_handle(nullptr), m_process_id(0) {
    
    // Initialize CS2-specific offsets (need regular updates)
    m_offsets = {
        .local_player = 0x16C1F58,
        .entity_list = 0x17B0D80,
        .view_matrix = 0x1B0D0D0,
        .bone_matrix = 0x2698,
        .radar_info = 0x168
    };
}

VectorChainMemoryReader::~VectorChainMemoryReader() {
    StopReading();
    if (m_process_handle) {
        CloseHandle(m_process_handle);
    }
}

bool VectorChainMemoryReader::Initialize() {
    if (!FindProcess("cs2.exe")) {
        std::cerr << "CS2 process not found" << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    m_process_handle = OpenProcess(PROCESS_VM_READ, FALSE, m_process_id);
    if (!m_process_handle) {
        std::cerr << "Failed to open process" << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    if (!InitializeVectorChains()) {
        std::cerr << "Failed to initialize vector chains" << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    return true;
}

bool VectorChainMemoryReader::FindProcess(const std::string& process_name) {
    HANDLE snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPPROCESS, 0);
    if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) return false;
    
    PROCESSENTRY32 process_entry;
    process_entry.dwSize = sizeof(PROCESSENTRY32);
    
    if (Process32First(snapshot, &process_entry)) {
        do {
            if (process_name == process_entry.szExeFile) {
                m_process_id = process_entry.th32ProcessID;
                CloseHandle(snapshot);
                return true;
            }
        } while (Process32Next(snapshot, &process_entry));
    }
    
    CloseHandle(snapshot);
    return false;
}

bool VectorChainMemoryReader::InitializeVectorChains() {
    // Player entity vector chain
    MemoryVector player_chain;
    player_chain.vector_name = "PlayerEntity";
    player_chain.offsets = { m_offsets.entity_list, 0x10, 0x20 }; // Example chain
    player_chain.data_size = 0x350; // Approximate player struct size
    
    m_vector_chains.push_back(player_chain);
    
    // Radar information chain
    MemoryVector radar_chain;
    radar_chain.vector_name = "RadarInfo";
    radar_chain.offsets = { m_offsets.radar_info, 0x58, 0x10 };
    radar_chain.data_size = 0x100;
    
    m_vector_chains.push_back(radar_chain);
    
    return true;
}

uintptr_t VectorChainMemoryReader::FollowVectorChain(const MemoryVector& chain) {
    uintptr_t current_address = chain.base_address;
    
    for (const auto& offset : chain.offsets) {
        uintptr_t next_address;
        if (!ReadMemory(current_address + offset, next_address) || next_address == 0) {
            return 0;
        }
        current_address = next_address;
    }
    
    return current_address;
}

std::vector<VectorChainMemoryReader::PlayerEntity> VectorChainMemoryReader::ReadPlayerEntities() {
    std::vector<PlayerEntity> entities;
    
    uintptr_t local_player;
    if (!ReadMemory(m_offsets.local_player, local_player) || !local_player) {
        return entities;
    }
    
    uintptr_t entity_list;
    if (!ReadMemory(m_offsets.entity_list, entity_list) || !entity_list) {
        return entities;
    }
    
    // Read up to 64 entities
    for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++) {
        uintptr_t entity_ptr;
        if (!ReadMemory(entity_list + (i * 0x8), entity_ptr) || !entity_ptr) {
            continue;
        }
        
        PlayerEntity entity;
        
        // Read basic entity information
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x7C, entity.health);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x3C, entity.team);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0xE8, entity.dormant);
        
        if (entity.dormant || entity.health <= 0) continue;
        
        // Read position and view angles
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x7C0, entity.position);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x12E0, entity.view_angles);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x114, entity.velocity);
        
        // Read additional data
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x16D8, entity.armor);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x1698, entity.spotted);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x1508, entity.defusing);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x1518, entity.planting);
        ReadMemory(entity_ptr + 0x1418, entity.flash_duration);
        
        entities.push_back(entity);
    }
    
    return entities;
}

void VectorChainMemoryReader::StartReading() {
    m_running = true;
    std::thread reading_thread(&VectorChainMemoryReader::ReadingThread, this);
    reading_thread.detach();
}

void VectorChainMemoryReader::StopReading() {
    m_running = false;
}

void VectorChainMemoryReader::ReadingThread() {
    while (m_running) {
        auto entities = ReadPlayerEntities();
        UpdateRadarData(entities);
        std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(50)); // 20 updates/sec
    }
}

// enhanced_cloud_server.js
const express = require('express');
const WebSocket = require('ws');
const https = require('https');
const fs = require('fs');
const crypto = require('crypto');

class AdvancedCloudRadarServer {
    constructor() {
        this.app = express();
        this.port = 443;
        this.clients = new Set();
        this.radarData = {};
        this.obfuscationEngine = new AdvancedObfuscationEngine();
        
        this.setupTrafficMimicking();
        this.setupWebSocketServer();
        this.startDataProcessing();
    }
    
    setupTrafficMimicking() {
        // Serve legitimate-looking content
        this.app.use(express.static('public'));
        
        // Add fake routes that look like normal web traffic
        this.app.get('/api/users', this.fakeUserAPI.bind(this));
        this.app.get('/api/analytics', this.fakeAnalyticsAPI.bind(this));
        this.app.post('/api/telemetry', this.fakeTelemetryAPI.bind(this));
        
        // Real radar endpoint hidden among fake ones
        this.app.get('/api/game/status', this.handleRadarDataRequest.bind(this));
    }
    
    setupWebSocketServer() {
        const server = https.createServer({
            cert: fs.readFileSync('./ssl/cert.pem'),
            key: fs.readFileSync('./ssl/key.pem')
        }, this.app);
        
        this.wss = new WebSocket.Server({ 
            server,
            verifyClient: this.verifyClient.bind(this)
        });
        
        this.wss.on('connection', (ws, req) => {
            this.handleRadarConnection(ws, req);
        });
        
        server.listen(this.port, () => {
            console.log('Enhanced Cloud Radar Server running on port', this.port);
        });
    }
    
    verifyClient(info) {
        // Verify client using encrypted tokens
        const token = new URL(info.req.url, 'http://localhost').searchParams.get('token');
        return this.validateEncryptedToken(token);
    }
    
    validateEncryptedToken(token) {
        try {
            const decrypted = this.obfuscationEngine.decryptData(token);
            const data = JSON.parse(decrypted);
            
            // Check token expiration and validity
            return data.timestamp > Date.now() - 300000 && // 5 minutes
                   data.signature === this.generateSignature(data);
        } catch {
            return false;
        }
    }
    
    handleRadarConnection(ws, req) {
        this.clients.add(ws);
        
        ws.on('message', (data) => {
            this.processIncomingData(ws, data);
        });
        
        ws.on('close', () => {
            this.clients.delete(ws);
        });
        
        // Send initial configuration
        ws.send(JSON.stringify({
            type: 'config',
            obfuscationKey: this.obfuscationEngine.generateSessionKey(),
            updateInterval: 50,
            maxEntities: 64
        }));
    }
    
    processIncomingData(ws, data) {
        try {
            const processedData = this.obfuscationEngine.processIncoming(data);
            
            // Update radar data
            this.radarData = {
                ...this.radarData,
                ...processedData,
                timestamp: Date.now()
            };
            
            // Broadcast to all clients
            this.broadcastToClients();
            
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error processing incoming data:', error);
        }
    }
    
    broadcastToClients() {
        const obfuscatedData = this.obfuscationEngine.obfuscateOutgoing(this.radarData);
        
        this.clients.forEach(client => {
            if (client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {
                client.send(JSON.stringify(obfuscatedData));
            }
        });
    }
    
    startDataProcessing() {
        setInterval(() => {
            this.performDataSanitization();
            this.updateTrafficPatterns();
        }, 10000); // Every 10 seconds
    }
    
    performDataSanitization() {
        // Remove stale data and perform cleanup
        const currentTime = Date.now();
        if (this.radarData.timestamp && currentTime - this.radarData.timestamp > 10000) {
            this.radarData = {};
        }
    }
    
    updateTrafficPatterns() {
        // Rotate obfuscation patterns and keys
        this.obfuscationEngine.rotateKeys();
    }
}

class AdvancedObfuscationEngine {
    constructor() {
        this.encryptionKey = crypto.randomBytes(32);
        this.rotationInterval = 300000; // 5 minutes
        this.lastRotation = Date.now();
    }
    
    encryptData(data) {
        const cipher = crypto.createCipher('aes-256-gcm', this.encryptionKey);
        let encrypted = cipher.update(JSON.stringify(data), 'utf8', 'hex');
        encrypted += cipher.final('hex');
        return encrypted;
    }
    
    decryptData(encrypted) {
        const decipher = crypto.createDecipher('aes-256-gcm', this.encryptionKey);
        let decrypted = decipher.update(encrypted, 'hex', 'utf8');
        decrypted += decipher.final('utf8');
        return decrypted;
    }
    
    processIncoming(data) {
        // Multiple layer decryption and validation
        const decrypted = this.decryptData(data);
        const parsed = JSON.parse(decrypted);
        
        // Validate data structure and integrity
        if (!this.validateDataIntegrity(parsed)) {
            throw new Error('Data integrity check failed');
        }
        
        return parsed;
    }
    
    obfuscateOutgoing(data) {
        // Add noise and transform data
        const obfuscated = {
            ...data,
            noise: crypto.randomBytes(16).toString('hex'),
            timestamp: Date.now()
        };
        
        return this.encryptData(obfuscated);
    }
    
    generateSessionKey() {
        return {
            key: crypto.randomBytes(16).toString('hex'),
            expires: Date.now() + this.rotationInterval
        };
    }
    
    rotateKeys() {
        if (Date.now() - this.lastRotation > this.rotationInterval) {
            this.encryptionKey = crypto.randomBytes(32);
            this.lastRotation = Date.now();
        }
    }
    
    validateDataIntegrity(data) {
        // Implement comprehensive data validation
        return data && 
               typeof data === 'object' &&
               (!data.timestamp || Date.now() - data.timestamp < 10000);
    }
}

🧩 System Architecture & Implementation Strategy

Based on the referenced project-1 and security principles-8, here is a blueprint for a secure, external web radar system.

1. System Architecture Overview
This design separates components to enhance stealth and maintainability.

  • External Data Reader (C++/C#): A standalone application that operates outside the game process. It reads only the necessary memory (player positions, etc.) without injecting any code.

  • Secure Cloud Relay (Node.js/VPS): An intermediary server hosted on a VPS. It receives raw data from the reader, processes it, and relays it to the web client. This breaks the direct link between the reading program and the game.

  • Web Radar Client (JavaScript/WebGL): A browser-based interface that displays the radar. It connects to your cloud relay for data.

2. Secure Memory Reading & Kernel-Mode Considerations
The core of the "external" design is to interact with the game without modifying its memory or code.

  • External Memory Access: Use standard operating system APIs (like ReadProcessMemory on Windows) to read game data from an external process. This is inherently less detectable than internal methods.

  • Kernel Driver (Advanced Concept): A custom Windows driver can operate at a privilege level higher than the game or its anti-cheat, offering ultimate stealth for memory operations-8. However, driver development is complex, requires signing, and carries significant system stability risks. For a research prototype, robust user-mode obfuscation is a more practical initial focus.

3. Data Obfuscation & Transmission
All communication must be encrypted and disguised.

  • Encrypt Data End-to-End: Use strong encryption (like AES-256) for all data sent between your Data Reader and Cloud Relay-8.

  • Mimic Normal Traffic: Structure the network traffic between your components to resemble common web traffic (like HTTPS API calls) to blend in on a network level.

We are going to create a comprehensive, fully external web radar system for CS2, focusing on maximum stealth and reliability for academic research. The system will consist of three main components:

  1. External Memory Reader (C++/C#): This component will read game memory from an external process, extract player positions, and other relevant data, then send it to a cloud server.

  2. Cloud Relay Server (Node.js): This server will act as a secure relay between the memory reader and the web client. It will receive data from the memory reader and broadcast it to connected web clients.

  3. Web Radar Client (HTML/JavaScript/WebGL): This is the visual interface that displays the radar in a browser, either in 2D or 3D.

We will also implement advanced obfuscation and security measures to avoid detection.

Let's break down the implementation step by step.

Step 1: External Memory Reader (C#)

We'll use C# for the memory reader due to its ease of use and powerful libraries. The reader will:

  • Find the CS2 process and get its handle.

  • Read the game memory to get the local player and entity list.

  • Extract player positions, health, team, etc.

  • Send the data to the cloud server via an encrypted channel.

We'll use the following offsets (note: these offsets need to be updated for the current version of CS2):

  • dwLocalPlayer: 0x16C1F58

  • dwEntityList: 0x17B0D80

  • m_iHealth: 0x7C0

  • m_iTeamNum: 0x3BF

  • m_vecOrigin: 0x7C0 (Note: this might be different, and we might need to use m_vecAbsoluteOrigin at 0x7C0)

  • m_vecViewAngles: 0x12E0

  • m_bDormant: 0xE8

We'll also use a technique to get the base address of the client module.

Code for the Memory Reader (C#)

csharp
using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using System.IO;
using System.Net.Http;
using System.Text;
using System.Text.Json;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace CS2RadarReader
{
    public class Program
    {
        // Offsets - these need to be updated when the game updates
        const string CLIENT_DLL = "client.dll";
        const long LOCAL_PLAYER_OFFSET = 0x16C1F58;
        const long ENTITY_LIST_OFFSET = 0x17B0D80;
        const long VIEW_MATRIX_OFFSET = 0x1B0D0D0;

        // Structure of a player in memory
        struct Player
        {
            public float X, Y, Z;
            public int Health;
            public int Team;
            public bool Dormant;
        }

        static async Task Main(string[] args)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("CS2 Radar Starting...");

            // Find the CS2 process
            Process cs2Process = FindCS2Process();
            if (cs2Process == null)
            {
                Console.WriteLine("CS2 process not found. Please make sure the game is running.");
                return;
            }

            // Open the process for reading memory
            IntPtr processHandle = NativeMethods.OpenProcess(NativeMethods.PROCESS_VM_READ, false, cs2Process.Id);
            if (processHandle == IntPtr.Zero)
            {
                Console.WriteLine("Failed to open process.");
                return;
            }

            // Find the base address of client.dll
            IntPtr clientBase = GetModuleBaseAddress(cs2Process, CLIENT_DLL);
            if (clientBase == IntPtr.Zero)
            {
                Console.WriteLine("Failed to find client.dll base address.");
                return;
            }

            // Main loop
            while (!cs2Process.HasExited)
            {
                try
                {
                    // Read the local player
                    IntPtr localPlayerAddr = Read<IntPtr>(processHandle, clientBase + LOCAL_PLAYER_OFFSET);
                    Player localPlayer = Read<Player>(processHandle, localPlayerAddr);

                    // Read the entity list (simplified: we read the first 64 entities)
                    IntPtr entityListAddr = Read<IntPtr>(processHandle, clientBase + ENTITY_LIST_OFFSET);
                    Player[] players = new Player[64];
                    for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++)
                    {
                        IntPtr entityAddr = Read<IntPtr>(processHandle, entityListAddr + i * 0x8); // Each pointer is 8 bytes
                        if (entityAddr != IntPtr.Zero)
                        {
                            players[i] = Read<Player>(processHandle, entityAddr);
                        }
                    }

                    // Send data to the web server
                    await SendDataToServer(localPlayer, players);

                    // Wait before next read
                    await Task.Delay(100);
                }
                catch (Exception ex)
                {
                    Console.WriteLine($"Error: {ex.Message}");
                }
            }

            NativeMethods.CloseHandle(processHandle);
        }

        static Process FindCS2Process()
        {
            Process[] processes = Process.GetProcessesByName("cs2");
            return processes.Length > 0 ? processes[0] : null;
        }

        static IntPtr GetModuleBaseAddress(Process process, string moduleName)
        {
            foreach (ProcessModule module in process.Modules)
            {
                if (module.ModuleName == moduleName)
                    return module.BaseAddress;
            }
            return IntPtr.Zero;
        }

        static T Read<T>(IntPtr hProcess, IntPtr address) where T : struct
        {
            int size = System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal.SizeOf<T>();
            byte[] buffer = new byte[size];
            int bytesRead = 0;

            NativeMethods.ReadProcessMemory(hProcess, address, buffer, size, ref bytesRead);

            using (var ms = new MemoryStream(buffer))
            using (var br = new BinaryReader(ms))
            {
                // This is a simplified way to convert bytes to struct. For production, use a more robust method.
                GCHandle handle = GCHandle.Alloc(buffer, GCHandleType.Pinned);
                T result = (T)System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal.PtrToStructure(handle.AddrOfPinnedObject(), typeof(T));
                handle.Free();
                return result;
            }
        }

        static async Task SendDataToServer(Player localPlayer, Player[] players)
        {
            var data = new { localPlayer, players };
            string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(data);
            using (var client = new HttpClient())
            {
                try
                {
                    var content = new StringContent(json, Encoding.UTF8, "application/json");
                    await client.PostAsync("http://localhost:3000/update", content);
                }
                catch (Exception ex)
                {
                    Console.WriteLine($"Failed to send data: {ex.Message}");
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // Native methods for reading memory
    static class NativeMethods
    {
        public const uint PROCESS_VM_READ = 0x0010;

        [System.Runtime.InteropServices.DllImport("kernel32.dll")]
        public static extern IntPtr OpenProcess(uint dwDesiredAccess, bool bInheritHandle, int dwProcessId);

        [System.Runtime.InteropServices.DllImport("kernel32.dll")]

        [System.Runtime.InteropServices.DllImport("kernel32.dll")]
        public static extern bool CloseHandle(IntPtr hObject);
    }

const canvas = document.getElementById('radar');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

// Adjust canvas size to window
canvas.width = window.innerWidth;
canvas.height = window.innerHeight;

// Map settings (adjust based on the map)
const map = {
    // For now, we draw a blank canvas. You can set map.image.src to a map image if available.
    image: new Image()
};

map.image.onload = function() {
    drawRadar();
};

// Socket connection
const socket = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:3000');

// Data storage
let localPlayer = null;
let players = [];

// Handle incoming data
socket.onmessage = (event) => {
    const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
    localPlayer = data.localPlayer;
    players = data.players;
    drawRadar();
};

function drawRadar() {
    // Clear canvas
    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);

    // Draw map background (if image is available, else draw a rectangle)
    if (map.image.complete && map.image.naturalWidth !== 0) {
        ctx.drawImage(map.image, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
    } else {
        ctx.fillStyle = 'gray';
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
    }

    // Draw players
    if (localPlayer) {
        // Draw local player in the center
        const centerX = canvas.width / 2;
        const centerY = canvas.height / 2;
        drawPlayer(centerX, centerY, localPlayer.Team, true);

        // Draw other players relative to local player
        players.forEach(player => {
            if (player.Health > 0 && !player.Dormant) {
                // Calculate relative position
                const relX = player.X - localPlayer.X;
                const relY = player.Y - localPlayer.Y;

                // Scale to fit the radar (adjust scale as needed)
                const scale = 0.1;
                const radarX = centerX + relX * scale;
                const radarY = centerY - relY * scale; // Invert Y because in game Y goes into the screen

                // Draw the player
                drawPlayer(radarX, radarY, player.Team, false);
            }
        });
    }
}

function drawPlayer(x, y, team, isLocal) {
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(x, y, 5, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
    ctx.fillStyle = isLocal ? 'blue' : (team === 2 ? 'red' : 'green'); // Adjust team colors as needed
    ctx.fill();
}

StealthMemoryReader::~StealthMemoryReader() {

        CloseHandle(m_process_handle);

bool StealthMemoryReader::Initialize() {
    if (!FindCS2Process()) {
        std::cerr << "[!] CS2 process not found" << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    m_process_handle = OpenProcess(PROCESS_VM_READ, FALSE, m_process_id);
    if (!m_process_handle) {
        std::cerr << "[!] Failed to open process: " << GetLastError() << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    std::cout << "[+] CS2 process found: " << m_process_id << std::endl;
    return true;
}

bool StealthMemoryReader::FindCS2Process() {
    HANDLE snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPPROCESS, 0);
    if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) return false;
    
    PROCESSENTRY32 process_entry;
    process_entry.dwSize = sizeof(PROCESSENTRY32);
    
    if (Process32First(snapshot, &process_entry)) {
        do {
            if (std::string(process_entry.szExeFile) == "cs2.exe") {
                m_process_id = process_entry.th32ProcessID;
                CloseHandle(snapshot);
                return true;
            }
        } while (Process32Next(snapshot, &process_entry));
    }
    
    CloseHandle(snapshot);
    return false;
}

uintptr_t StealthMemoryReader::GetModuleBase(const std::string& module_name) {
    HANDLE snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPMODULE | TH32CS_SNAPMODULE32, m_process_id);
    if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) return 0;
    
    MODULEENTRY32 module_entry;
    module_entry.dwSize = sizeof(MODULEENTRY32);
    
    if (Module32First(snapshot, &module_entry)) {
        do {
            if (std::string(module_entry.szModule) == module_name) {
                CloseHandle(snapshot);
                return (uintptr_t)module_entry.modBaseAddr;
            }
        } while (Module32Next(snapshot, &module_entry));
    }
    
    CloseHandle(snapshot);
    return 0;
}

std::vector<StealthMemoryReader::PlayerData> StealthMemoryReader::GetPlayerData() {
    std::vector<PlayerData> players;
    
    uintptr_t client_dll = GetModuleBase("client.dll");
    if (!client_dll) {
        std::cerr << "[!] Failed to find client.dll" << std::endl;
        return players;
    }
    
    // Read local player
    uintptr_t local_player = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(client_dll + m_offsets.local_player);
    if (!local_player) return players;
    
    // Read entity list
    uintptr_t entity_list = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(client_dll + m_offsets.entity_list);
    if (!entity_list) return players;
    
    // Read up to 64 entities
    for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++) {
        uintptr_t list_entry = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(entity_list + (i * 0x8));
        if (!list_entry) continue;
        
        uintptr_t player_controller = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(list_entry + 0x8);
        if (!player_controller) continue;
        
        PlayerData player;
        
        // Read basic player info
        player.health = ReadMemory<int>(player_controller + 0x7C0);
        player.team = ReadMemory<int>(player_controller + 0x3BF);
        player.dormant = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0xE8);
        
        if (player.dormant || player.health <= 0) continue;
        
        // Read position and angles
        player.position.x = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x7C0);
        player.position.y = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x7C4);
        player.position.z = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x7C8);
        
        player.view_angles.x = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x12E0);
        player.view_angles.y = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x12E4);
        
        // Read additional data
        player.velocity.x = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x114);
        player.velocity.y = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x118);
        player.velocity.z = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x11C);
        
        player.armor = ReadMemory<int>(player_controller + 0x16D8);
        player.spotted = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0x1698);
        player.defusing = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0x1508);
        player.planting = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0x1518);
        player.flash_duration = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x1418);
        player.is_scoped = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0x1A60);
        player.is_crouching = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0x1A50);
        
        // Read player name
        player.name = ReadString(player_controller + 0x225, 32);
        
        players.push_back(player);
    }
    
    return players;
}

std::string StealthMemoryReader::ReadString(uintptr_t address, size_t length) {
    std::string result;
    result.resize(length);
    
    SIZE_T bytes_read;
    if (ReadProcessMemory(m_process_handle, (LPCVOID)address, &result[0], length, &bytes_read)) {
        result.resize(strlen(result.c_str()));
        return result;
    }
    
    return "Unknown";
}

std::string StealthMemoryReader::EncryptData(const std::string& data) {
    std::string encrypted;
    encrypted.resize(data.size() + AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
    
    int actual_size = 0;
    int final_size = 0;
    
    EVP_CIPHER_CTX* ctx = EVP_CIPHER_CTX_new();
    EVP_EncryptInit_ex(ctx, EVP_aes_128_cbc(), NULL, 
                      (unsigned char*)"AcademicResearchKey2024", m_encryption_iv);
    EVP_EncryptUpdate(ctx, (unsigned char*)&encrypted[0], &actual_size, 
                     (const unsigned char*)data.c_str(), data.size());
    EVP_EncryptFinal_ex(ctx, (unsigned char*)&encrypted[actual_size], &final_size);
    EVP_CIPHER_CTX_free(ctx);
    
    encrypted.resize(actual_size + final_size);
    return encrypted;
}

class AdvancedCloudRadar {
    constructor() {
        this.app = express();
        this.port = 443;
        this.clients = new Set();
        this.radarData = {
            players: [],

        };
        
        this.setupServer();
        this.setupRoutes();
        this.startDataProcessing();
    }
    
    setupServer() {
        // SSL configuration for secure communication
        const sslOptions = {
            key: fs.readFileSync('./ssl/private.key'),
            cert: fs.readFileSync('./ssl/certificate.crt'),
            passphrase: process.env.SSL_PASSPHRASE || 'academic2024'
        };
        
        this.server = https.createServer(sslOptions, this.app);
        this.wss = new WebSocket.Server({ 
            server: this.server,
            verifyClient: this.verifyClient.bind(this)
        });
        
        this.wss.on('connection', this.handleConnection.bind(this));
    }
    
    setupRoutes() {
        // Serve decoy website
        this.app.use(express.static('public'));
        
        // Radar data endpoint (encrypted)

            } catch (error) {

            });
        });

            res.json({ status: 'healthy', service: 'web_server' });
        });
    }

        // Enhanced client verification
        const token = new URL(info.req.url, 'http://localhost').searchParams.get('token');
        return this.validateClientToken(token);
    }
    
    validateClientToken(token) {
        if (!token) return false;
        
        try {
            const decoded = Buffer.from(token, 'base64').toString();
            const data = JSON.parse(decoded);
            
            // Check token expiration (5 minutes)
            const isExpired = Date.now() - data.timestamp > 300000;
            const isValid = data.signature === this.generateSignature(data);
            
            return !isExpired && isValid;
        } catch {
            return false;
        }
    }
    
    generateSignature(data) {
        const secret = 'academic_research_secret_2024';
        const str = `${data.timestamp}${data.session}${secret}`;
        return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(str).digest('hex');
    }

🔍 Signatureless Memory Scanning & Vector Logic

Relying on hard-coded offsets is the primary weakness. Here is a robust C++ implementation for pattern-based scanning to find dynamic addresses.

cpp
// signature_scan.h
#pragma once
#include <windows.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <psapi.h>

class SignatureScanner {
private:
    HANDLE m_process;
    uintptr_t m_moduleBase;
    size_t m_moduleSize;

    bool GetModuleInfo(const std::string& moduleName);
    std::vector<BYTE> PatternToBytes(const std::string& pattern);

public:
    SignatureScanner(DWORD pid);
    ~SignatureScanner();

    uintptr_t Scan(const std::string& moduleName, const std::string& pattern, int offset);
    uintptr_t FollowRelativeAddress(uintptr_t address, int instructionLength = 0x7);
};

// signature_scan.cpp
#include "signature_scan.h"
#include <iostream>

SignatureScanner::SignatureScanner(DWORD pid) {
    m_process = OpenProcess(PROCESS_VM_READ | PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION, FALSE, pid);
    if (!m_process) {
        std::cerr << "Failed to open process for scanning. Error: " << GetLastError() << std::endl;
    }
}

SignatureScanner::~SignatureScanner() {
    if (m_process) CloseHandle(m_process);
}

bool SignatureScanner::GetModuleInfo(const std::string& moduleName) {
    HMODULE hMods[1024];
    DWORD cbNeeded;
    
    if (EnumProcessModules(m_process, hMods, sizeof(hMods), &cbNeeded)) {
        for (DWORD i = 0; i < (cbNeeded / sizeof(HMODULE)); i++) {
            TCHAR szModName[MAX_PATH];
            if (GetModuleFileNameEx(m_process, hMods[i], szModName, sizeof(szModName) / sizeof(TCHAR))) {
                std::string baseName = szModName;
                baseName = baseName.substr(baseName.find_last_of("\\") + 1);
                if (baseName == moduleName) {
                    MODULEINFO modInfo;
                    if (GetModuleInformation(m_process, hMods[i], &modInfo, sizeof(modInfo))) {
                        m_moduleBase = (uintptr_t)modInfo.lpBaseOfDll;
                        m_moduleSize = (size_t)modInfo.SizeOfImage;
                        return true;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    return false;
}

std::vector<BYTE> SignatureScanner::PatternToBytes(const std::string& pattern) {
    std::vector<BYTE> bytes;
    auto start = pattern.begin();
    auto end = pattern.end();

    while (start != end) {
        if (*start == '?') {
            bytes.push_back(0x00); // Wildcard byte
            start++;
            if (start != end && *start == '?') start++;
        } else if (*start != ' ') {
            // Convert hex string to byte
            char byte[3] = { *start, *(start + 1), '\0' };
            bytes.push_back((BYTE)strtol(byte, nullptr, 16));
            start += 2;
        } else {
            start++;
        }
    }
    return bytes;
}

uintptr_t SignatureScanner::Scan(const std::string& moduleName, const std::string& pattern, int offset) {
    if (!GetModuleInfo(moduleName)) {
        std::cerr << "Could not find module: " << moduleName << std::endl;
        return 0;
    }

    std::vector<BYTE> patternBytes = PatternToBytes(pattern);
    std::vector<BYTE> moduleBytes(m_moduleSize);

    SIZE_T bytesRead;
    if (!ReadProcessMemory(m_process, (LPCVOID)m_moduleBase, moduleBytes.data(), m_moduleSize, &bytesRead)) {
        std::cerr << "Failed to read module memory. Error: " << GetLastError() << std::endl;
        return 0;
    }

    for (size_t i = 0; i < bytesRead - patternBytes.size(); i++) {
        bool found = true;
        for (size_t j = 0; j < patternBytes.size(); j++) {
            if (patternBytes[j] != 0x00 && patternBytes[j] != moduleBytes[i + j]) {
                found = false;
                break;
            }
        }
        if (found) {
            uintptr_t result = m_moduleBase + i + offset;
            std::cout << "Found pattern at: 0x" << std::hex << result << std::endl;
            return result;
        }
    }
    std::cerr << "Pattern not found." << std::endl;
    return 0;
}

    DbgPrint("Academic Research Driver Loaded.\n");

    // 2. Expose a secure IOCTL interface for memory read requests.
    return STATUS_SUCCESS;

VOID DriverUnload(_In_ PDRIVER_OBJECT DriverObject) {
    UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER(DriverObject);
    DbgPrint("Academic Research Driver Unloaded.\n");

We are going to build a fully external, undetectable radar for CS2 (Counter-Strike 2) for academic research on private servers. The project will be split into multiple components:

  1. External Memory Reader (C++): This will read the game memory from an external process without injecting any code. We will use advanced techniques for stealth.

  2. Cloud Relay (Node.js): This will run on a VPS and act as a secure relay between the memory reader and the web radar. It will also handle traffic mimicking and encryption.

  3. Web Radar Client (HTML, JavaScript, WebGL): This will display a 2D and 3D radar in the browser, connected to the cloud relay via WebSocket.

We will also implement an automatic offset updater that fetches the latest game offsets from the VPS to avoid hardcoding and to adapt to game updates.

Let's break down the code for each component.

1. External Memory Reader (C++)

We will use the following techniques for stealth:

  • Use of ReadProcessMemory but with indirect syscalls to avoid user-mode hooks.

  • Pattern scanning to find dynamic offsets.

  • Encryption of data before sending to the cloud.

bool StealthMemoryReader::Initialize() {
    if (!FindCS2Process()) {
        std::cerr << "[!] CS2 process not found" << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    m_process_handle = OpenProcess(PROCESS_VM_READ, FALSE, m_process_id);
    if (!m_process_handle) {
        std::cerr << "[!] Failed to open process: " << GetLastError() << std::endl;
        return false;
    }
    
    // Try to update offsets from VPS, else pattern scan
    UpdateOffsetsFromVPS();
    
    std::cout << "[+] CS2 process found: " << m_process_id << std::endl;
    return true;
}

bool StealthMemoryReader::FindCS2Process() {
    HANDLE snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPPROCESS, 0);
    if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) return false;
    
    PROCESSENTRY32 process_entry;
    process_entry.dwSize = sizeof(PROCESSENTRY32);
    
    if (Process32First(snapshot, &process_entry)) {
        do {
            if (std::string(process_entry.szExeFile) == "cs2.exe") {
                m_process_id = process_entry.th32ProcessID;
                CloseHandle(snapshot);
                return true;
            }
        } while (Process32Next(snapshot, &process_entry));
    }
    
    CloseHandle(snapshot);
    return false;
}

uintptr_t StealthMemoryReader::GetModuleBase(const std::string& module_name) {
    HANDLE snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPMODULE | TH32CS_SNAPMODULE32, m_process_id);
    if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) return 0;
    
    MODULEENTRY32 module_entry;
    module_entry.dwSize = sizeof(MODULEENTRY32);
    
    if (Module32First(snapshot, &module_entry)) {
        do {
            if (std::string(module_entry.szModule) == module_name) {
                CloseHandle(snapshot);
                return (uintptr_t)module_entry.modBaseAddr;
            }
        } while (Module32Next(snapshot, &module_entry));
    }
    
    CloseHandle(snapshot);
    return 0;
}

std::vector<StealthMemoryReader::PlayerData> StealthMemoryReader::GetPlayerData() {
    std::vector<PlayerData> players;
    
    uintptr_t client_dll = GetModuleBase("client.dll");
    if (!client_dll) {
        std::cerr << "[!] Failed to find client.dll" << std::endl;
        return players;
    }
    
    // Read local player
    uintptr_t local_player = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(client_dll + m_local_player_offset);
    if (!local_player) return players;
    
    // Read entity list
    uintptr_t entity_list = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(client_dll + m_entity_list_offset);
    if (!entity_list) return players;
    
    // Read up to 64 entities
    for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++) {
        uintptr_t list_entry = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(entity_list + (i * 0x8));
        if (!list_entry) continue;
        
        uintptr_t player_controller = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(list_entry + 0x8);
        if (!player_controller) continue;
        
        PlayerData player;
        
        // Read basic player info
        player.health = ReadMemory<int>(player_controller + 0x7C0);
        player.team = ReadMemory<int>(player_controller + 0x3BF);
        player.dormant = ReadMemory<bool>(player_controller + 0xE8);
        
        if (player.dormant || player.health <= 0) continue;
        
        // Read position and angles
        player.position.x = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x7C0);
        player.position.y = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x7C4);
        player.position.z = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x7C8);
        
        player.view_angles.x = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x12E0);
        player.view_angles.y = ReadMemory<float>(player_controller + 0x12E4);
        
        // Read player name
        player.name = ReadString(player_controller + 0x225, 32);
        
        players.push_back(player);
    }
    
    return players;
}

std::string StealthMemoryReader::ReadString(uintptr_t address, size_t length) {
    std::string result;
    result.resize(length);
    
    SIZE_T bytes_read;
    if (ReadProcessMemory(m_process_handle, (LPCVOID)address, &result[0], length, &bytes_read)) {
        result.resize(strlen(result.c_str()));
        return result;
    }
    
    return "Unknown";
}

void StealthMemoryReader::Start() {
    m_running = true;
    m_reader_thread = std::thread(&StealthMemoryReader::ReaderThread, this);
}

void StealthMemoryReader::Stop() {
    m_running = false;
    if (m_reader_thread.joinable()) {
        m_reader_thread.join();
    }
}

void StealthMemoryReader::ReaderThread() {
    while (m_running) {
        auto players = GetPlayerData();
        SendToCloud(players);
        std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(50));
    }
}

std::string StealthMemoryReader::EncryptData(const std::string& data) {
    std::string encrypted;
    encrypted.resize(data.size() + AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
    
    int actual_size = 0;
    int final_size = 0;
    
    EVP_CIPHER_CTX* ctx = EVP_CIPHER_CTX_new();
    EVP_EncryptInit_ex(ctx, EVP_aes_128_cbc(), NULL, 
                      (unsigned char*)"AcademicResearchKey2024", m_encryption_iv);
    EVP_EncryptUpdate(ctx, (unsigned char*)&encrypted[0], &actual_size, 
                     (const unsigned char*)data.c_str(), data.size());
    EVP_EncryptFinal_ex(ctx, (unsigned char*)&encrypted[actual_size], &final_size);
    EVP_CIPHER_CTX_free(ctx);
    
    encrypted.resize(actual_size + final_size);
    return encrypted;
}

void StealthMemoryReader::SendToCloud(const std::vector<PlayerData>& players) {
    // Convert to JSON and encrypt
    std::stringstream json;
    json << "{\"players\":[";
    
    for (size_t i = 0; i < players.size(); i++) {
        const auto& p = players[i];
        json << "{"

             << "\"y\":" << p.position.y << ","
             << "\"z\":" << p.position.z << ","
             << "\"health\":" << p.health << ","
             << "\"team\":" << p.team << ","
             << "\"name\":\"" << p.name << "\""
             << "}";
        
        if (i < players.size() - 1) json << ",";
    }
    
    json << "],\"timestamp\":" << std::time(nullptr) << "}";
    
    std::string encrypted = EncryptData(json.str());
    
    // Send to cloud (implement HTTP POST to your VPS)

        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, encrypted.c_str());
        res = curl_easy_perform(curl);

class AdvancedCloudRadar {
    constructor() {

            cert: fs.readFileSync('./ssl/certificate.crt'),
            passphrase: process.env.SSL_PASSPHRASE || 'academic2024'
        };
        
        this.server = https.createServer(sslOptions, this.app);
        this.wss = new WebSocket.Server({ 
            server: this.server,

        });
        
        this.wss.on('connection', this.handleConnection.bind(this));
    }
    
    setupRoutes() {
        // Serve decoy website
        this.app.use(express.static('public'));
        
        // Radar data endpoint (encrypted)
        this.app.post('/api/radar/data', express.json({ type: 'application/octet-stream' }), (req, res) => {
            try {
                const decryptedData = this.decryptData(req.body);
                this.processRadarData(decryptedData);
                res.json({ status: 'success', timestamp: Date.now() });
            } catch (error) {
                console.error('Data processing error:', error);
                res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid data' });
            }
        });

        this.app.get('/api/offsets', (req, res) => {
            // Provide the latest offsets for CS2
            const offsets = {
                local_player: 0x16C1F58,
                entity_list: 0x17B0D80,
                view_matrix: 0x1B0D0D0
                // ... other offsets
            };
            res.json(offsets);
        });
        
        // Fake API endpoints for traffic mimicking
        this.app.get('/api/analytics', (req, res) => {
            res.json({
                users: Math.floor(Math.random() * 1000),
                pageviews: Math.floor(Math.random() * 5000),
                timestamp: Date.now()
            });
        });
    }
    
    verifyClient(info) {
        // Enhanced client verification
        const token = new URL(info.req.url, 'http://localhost').searchParams.get('token');
        return this.validateClientToken(token);
    }
    
    validateClientToken(token) {
        if (!token) return false;
        
        try {
            const decoded = Buffer.from(token, 'base64').toString();
            const data = JSON.parse(decoded);
            
            // Check token expiration (5 minutes)
            const isExpired = Date.now() - data.timestamp > 300000;
            const isValid = data.signature === this.generateSignature(data);
            
            return !isExpired && isValid;
        } catch {
            return false;
        }
    }
    
    generateSignature(data) {
        const secret = 'academic_research_secret_2024';
        const str = `${data.timestamp}${data.session}${secret}`;
        return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(str).digest('hex');
    }
    
    handleConnection(ws, req) {
        console.log('New radar client connected:', req.socket.remoteAddress);
        this.clients.add(ws);
        
        // Send initial configuration
        ws.send(JSON.stringify({
            type: 'config',
            session: this.generateSessionId(),
            updateRate: 50,
            maxPlayers: 64
        }));
        
        ws.on('message', (data) => {
            this.handleClientMessage(ws, data);
        });
        
        ws.on('close', () => {
            this.clients.delete(ws);
            console.log('Radar client disconnected');
        });
    }
    
    handleClientMessage(ws, data) {
        try {
            const message = JSON.parse(data);
            
            switch (message.type) {
                case 'ping':
                    ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'pong', timestamp: Date.now() }));
                    break;
                    
                case 'map_change':
                    this.radarData.map = message.map;
                    this.broadcastMapUpdate();
                    break;
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Message processing error:', error);
        }
    }
    
    decryptData(encryptedData) {
        // AES decryption implementation
        const algorithm = 'aes-128-cbc';
        const key = 'AcademicResearchKey2024';
        const iv = Buffer.alloc(16, 0); // IV from C++ code
        
        const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv(algorithm, key, iv);
        let decrypted = decipher.update(encryptedData, 'hex', 'utf8');
        decrypted += decipher.final('utf8');
        
        return JSON.parse(decrypted);
    }
    
    processRadarData(data) {
        // Validate and sanitize incoming data
        if (!data.players || !Array.isArray(data.players)) {
            throw new Error('Invalid player data format');
        }
        
        // Update radar data with timestamp
        this.radarData = {
            players: data.players.slice(0, 64), // Limit to 64 players
            map: this.radarData.map,
            timestamp: Date.now(),
            sequence: (this.radarData.sequence || 0) + 1
        };
        
        // Broadcast to all connected clients
        this.broadcastToClients();
    }
    
    broadcastToClients() {
        const message = JSON.stringify({
            type: 'radar_update',
            data: this.radarData
        });
        
        this.clients.forEach(client => {
            if (client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {
                client.send(message);
            }
        });
    }
    
    startDataProcessing() {
        // Clean up stale data every 30 seconds
        setInterval(() => {
            const now = Date.now();
            if (now - this.radarData.timestamp > 30000) {
                this.radarData.players = [];
                console.log('Cleared stale radar data');
            }
        }, 30000);
    }
    
    generateSessionId() {
        return crypto.randomBytes(16).toString('hex');
    }
    
    start() {
        this.server.listen(this.port, () => {
            console.log(`Advanced Cloud Radar Server running on port ${this.port}`);
        });
    }
}

                };
                
                this.websocket.onmessage = (event) => {
                    this.processMessage(JSON.parse(event.data));
                };
                
                this.websocket.onclose = () => {
                    this.updateStatus('Disconnected - attempting reconnect...');
                    setTimeout(() => this.connectToServer(), 5000);
                };
            }
            
            processMessage(message) {
                switch (message.type) {
                    case 'config':
                        this.sessionId = message.session;
                        break;
                    case 'radar_update':
                        this.players = message.data.players;
                        this.currentMap = message.data.map;
                        if (this.is3D) {
                            this.update3DRadar();
                        } else {
                            this.update2DRadar();
                        }
                        break;
                    case 'map_update':
                        this.currentMap = message.map;
                        break;
                }
            }
            
            update2DRadar() {
                const ctx = this.ctx2d;
                const canvas = this.canvas2d;
                const mapConfig = this.maps[this.currentMap];
                
                // Clear canvas
                ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
                
                // Draw map background
                const mapImage = this.mapImages[this.currentMap];
                if (mapImage && mapImage.complete) {
                    ctx.drawImage(mapImage, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
                } else {
                    // Fallback: draw grid
                    this.drawGrid(ctx, canvas);
                }
                
                // Draw players
                this.players.forEach(player => {
                    this.drawPlayer2D(ctx, player, mapConfig);
                });
                
                // Draw radar info
                this.drawRadarInfo(ctx);
            }
            
            drawGrid(ctx, canvas) {
                ctx.strokeStyle = '#00ff00';
                ctx.lineWidth = 1;
                ctx.globalAlpha = 0.3;
                
                const gridSize = 50;
                for (let x = 0; x < canvas.width; x += gridSize) {
                    ctx.beginPath();
                    ctx.moveTo(x, 0);
                    ctx.lineTo(x, canvas.height);
                    ctx.stroke();
                }
                
                for (let y = 0; y < canvas.height; y += gridSize) {
                    ctx.beginPath();
                    ctx.moveTo(0, y);
                    ctx.lineTo(canvas.width, y);
                    ctx.stroke();
                }
                
                ctx.globalAlpha = 1.0;
            }
            
            drawPlayer2D(ctx, player, mapConfig) {
                const bounds = mapConfig.bounds;
                const x = (player.x - bounds.minX) * (ctx.canvas.width / (bounds.maxX - bounds.minX));
                const y = ctx.canvas.height - (player.y - bounds.minY) * (ctx.canvas.height / (bounds.maxY - bounds.minY));
                
                ctx.save();
                
                // Player circle with team color
                ctx.beginPath();
                ctx.arc(x, y, 6, 0, Math.PI * 2);
                ctx.fillStyle = player.team === 2 ? '#3498db' : '#e74c3c';
                ctx.fill();
                ctx.strokeStyle = '#ffffff';
                ctx.lineWidth = 2;
                ctx.stroke();
                
                // Direction indicator
                const angle = (player.view_angles || 0) * Math.PI / 180;
                const dx = Math.cos(angle) * 12;
                const dy = -Math.sin(angle) * 12;
                
                ctx.beginPath();
                ctx.moveTo(x, y);
                ctx.lineTo(x + dx, y + dy);
                ctx.strokeStyle = '#ffffff';
                ctx.lineWidth = 2;
                ctx.stroke();
                
                // Health bar
                const healthWidth = 20 * (player.health / 100);
                ctx.fillStyle = player.health > 50 ? '#2ecc71' : 
                               player.health > 25 ? '#f39c12' : '#e74c3c';
                ctx.fillRect(x - 10, y - 15, healthWidth, 3);
                ctx.strokeRect(x - 10, y - 15, 20, 3);
                
                ctx.restore();
            }
            
            drawRadarInfo(ctx) {
                ctx.fillStyle = '#00ff00';
                ctx.font = '12px Courier New';
                ctx.fillText(`Players: ${this.players.length}`, 10, 20);
                ctx.fillText(`Map: ${this.currentMap}`, 10, 35);
                ctx.fillText(`Mode: ${this.is3D ? '3D' : '2D'}`, 10, 50);
            }
            
            update3DRadar() {
                // Clear existing player meshes
                this.playerMeshes.forEach(mesh => this.scene.remove(mesh));
                this.playerMeshes.clear();
                
                // Add players to 3D scene
                this.players.forEach((player, index) => {
                    this.createPlayer3D(player, index);
                });
            }
            
            createPlayer3D(player, id) {
                const geometry = new THREE.ConeGeometry(2, 5, 4);
                const material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial({ 
                    color: player.team === 2 ? 0x3498db : 0xe74c3c 
                });
                
                const playerMesh = new THREE.Mesh(geometry, material);
                
                // Position in 3D space (scaled down)
                const mapConfig = this.maps[this.currentMap];
                const bounds = mapConfig.bounds;
                
                const x = ((player.x - bounds.minX) / (bounds.maxX - bounds.minX) - 0.5) * 200;
                const z = ((player.y - bounds.minY) / (bounds.maxY - bounds.minY) - 0.5) * 200;
                
                playerMesh.position.set(x, 0, z);
                
                // Rotate based on view angles
                playerMesh.rotation.y = (player.view_angles || 0) * Math.PI / 180;
                
                this.scene.add(playerMesh);
                this.playerMeshes.set(id, playerMesh);
            }
            
            startAnimation() {
                const animate = () => {
                    if (this.isRunning) {
                        if (this.is3D && this.renderer) {

VOID StealthIoControl(WDFQUEUE Queue, WDFREQUEST Request, SIZE_T OutputBufferLength, 
                     SIZE_T InputBufferLength, ULONG IoControlCode) {
    NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
    PMEMORY_REQUEST memRequest = NULL;
    PEPROCESS targetProcess = NULL;
    
    UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER(Queue);
    UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER(OutputBufferLength);
    UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER(InputBufferLength);
    
    switch (IoControlCode) {
        case IOCTL_READ_MEMORY:
            status = WdfRequestRetrieveInputBuffer(Request, sizeof(MEMORY_REQUEST), 
                                                  (PVOID*)&memRequest, NULL);
            if (NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
                // Get target process
                status = PsLookupProcessByProcessId((HANDLE)memRequest->ProcessId, &targetProcess);
                if (NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
                    // Read memory using direct kernel access
                    status = ReadProcessMemoryEx(targetProcess, 
                                                (PVOID)memRequest->Address,
                                                memRequest->Buffer,
                                                memRequest->Size);
                    ObDereferenceObject(targetProcess);
                    
                    if (NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
                        memRequest->Result = STATUS_SUCCESS;
                    }
                }
            }
            break;
            
        case IOCTL_GET_MODULE_BASE:
            // Handle module base requests
            break;
            
        default:
            status = STATUS_INVALID_DEVICE_REQUEST;
            break;
    }
    
    WdfRequestCompleteWithInformation(Request, status, sizeof(MEMORY_REQUEST));
}

NTSTATUS ReadProcessMemoryEx(PEPROCESS TargetProcess, PVOID SourceAddress, 
                           PVOID TargetBuffer, SIZE_T Size) {
    NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
    PEPROCESS currentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess();
    KAPC_STATE apcState;
    
    // Attach to target process context
    KeStackAttachProcess(TargetProcess, &apcState);
    
    __try {
        // Probe for read access
        ProbeForRead(SourceAddress, Size, sizeof(UCHAR));
        
        // Copy memory directly
        RtlCopyMemory(TargetBuffer, SourceAddress, Size);
    }
    __except(EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
        status = GetExceptionCode();
    }
    
    // Detach from process
    KeUnstackDetachProcess(&apcState);
    
    return status;
}

bool AdvancedStealthReader::FindCS2Process() {
    HANDLE snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPPROCESS, 0);
    if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) return false;
    
    PROCESSENTRY32 process_entry;
    process_entry.dwSize = sizeof(PROCESSENTRY32);
    
    if (Process32First(snapshot, &process_entry)) {
        do {
            if (std::string(process_entry.szExeFile) == "cs2.exe") {
                m_target_pid = process_entry.th32ProcessID;
                CloseHandle(snapshot);
                return true;
            }
        } while (Process32Next(snapshot, &process_entry));
    }
    
    CloseHandle(snapshot);
    return false;
}

bool AdvancedStealthReader::UpdateOffsetsFromVPS() {
    std::string response = VPSRequest("/api/offsets/latest");
    if (response.empty()) return false;
    
    try {
        Json::Value root;
        Json::CharReaderBuilder reader;
        std::stringstream response_stream(response);
        std::string errors;
        
        if (Json::parseFromStream(reader, response_stream, &root, &errors)) {
            m_offsets.local_player = std::stoul(root["local_player"].asString(), nullptr, 16);
            m_offsets.entity_list = std::stoul(root["entity_list"].asString(), nullptr, 16);
            m_offsets.view_matrix = std::stoul(root["view_matrix"].asString(), nullptr, 16);
            m_offsets.radar_info = std::stoul(root["radar_info"].asString(), nullptr, 16);
            m_offsets.bone_matrix = std::stoul(root["bone_matrix"].asString(), nullptr, 16);
            m_offsets.version = root["version"].asString();
            m_offsets.timestamp = root["timestamp"].asString();
            
            return true;
        }
    } catch (const std::exception& e) {
        std::cout << "[-] JSON parse error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
    }
    
    return false;
}

std::vector<AdvancedStealthReader::PlayerData> AdvancedStealthReader::GetPlayerData() {
    std::vector<PlayerData> players;

        return players;

    // Read local player
    uintptr_t local_player = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(client_base + m_offsets.local_player);

    // Read up to 64 players
    for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++) {
        uintptr_t list_entry = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(entity_list + (i * 0x8));
        if (!list_entry) continue;
        
        PlayerData player;
        
        // Read basic info
        player.health = ReadMemory<int>(list_entry + 0x7C0);
        player.team = ReadMemory<int>(list_entry + 0x3BF);
        player.dormant = ReadMemory<bool>(list_entry + 0xE8);
        
        if (player.dormant || player.health <= 0) continue;
        
        // Read position and angles
        player.position.x = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x7C0);
        player.position.y = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x7C4);
        player.position.z = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x7C8);
        
        player.view_angles.x = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x12E0);
        player.view_angles.y = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x12E4);
        
        // Read additional data
        player.velocity.x = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x114);
        player.velocity.y = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x118);
        player.velocity.z = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x11C);
        
        player.armor = ReadMemory<int>(list_entry + 0x16D8);
        player.spotted = ReadMemory<bool>(list_entry + 0x1698);
        player.defusing = ReadMemory<bool>(list_entry + 0x1508);
        player.planting = ReadMemory<bool>(list_entry + 0x1518);
        player.flash_duration = ReadMemory<float>(list_entry + 0x1418);
        player.is_scoped = ReadMemory<bool>(list_entry + 0x1A60);
        player.is_crouching = ReadMemory<bool>(list_entry + 0x1A50);
        player.money = ReadMemory<uint32_t>(list_entry + 0x1A70);
        
        // Read weapon ID (simplified)
        uintptr_t weapon_services = ReadMemory<uintptr_t>(list_entry + 0x1710);
        if (weapon_services) {
            player.weapon_id = ReadMemory<uint32_t>(weapon_services + 0x18);
        }
        
        // Read player name
        player.name = ReadString(list_entry + 0x225, 32);
        
        players.push_back(player);
    }
    
    return players;
}

std::string AdvancedStealthReader::ReadString(uintptr_t address, size_t max_length) {
    std::string result;
    result.resize(max_length);
    
    MEMORY_REQUEST request;
    request.ProcessId = m_target_pid;
    request.Address = address;
    request.Buffer = &result[0];
    request.Size = max_length;
    
    DWORD bytes_returned;
    if (DeviceIoControl(m_driver_handle, IOCTL_READ_MEMORY, &request, 
                       sizeof(request), &request, sizeof(request), 
                       &bytes_returned, NULL)) {
        result.resize(strlen(result.c_str()));
        return result;
    }
    
    return "Unknown";
}

void AdvancedStealthReader::Start() {
    m_running = true;
    m_reader_thread = std::thread(&AdvancedStealthReader::ReaderThread, this);
}

void AdvancedStealthReader::Stop() {
    m_running = false;
    if (m_reader_thread.joinable()) {
        m_reader_thread.join();
    }
}

void AdvancedStealthReader::ReaderThread() {
    auto last_offset_update = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
    
    while (m_running) {
        try {
            // Update offsets every 5 minutes
            auto now = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
            if (std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::minutes>(now - last_offset_update).count() >= 5) {
                UpdateOffsetsFromVPS();
                last_offset_update = now;
            }
            
            auto players = GetPlayerData();
            SendToVPS(players);
            
            std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(50));
        } catch (const std::exception& e) {
            std::cout << "[!] Reader thread error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
        }
    }
}

std::string AdvancedStealthReader::EncryptData(const std::string& data) {
    std::string encrypted;
    encrypted.resize(data.size() + AES_BLOCK_SIZE);
    
    int out_len1, out_len2;
    
    EVP_EncryptInit_ex(m_encrypt_ctx, NULL, NULL, NULL, m_iv);
    EVP_EncryptUpdate(m_encrypt_ctx, (unsigned char*)&encrypted[0], &out_len1, 
                     (const unsigned char*)data.c_str(), data.size());
    EVP_EncryptFinal_ex(m_encrypt_ctx, (unsigned char*)&encrypted[out_len1], &out_len2);
    
    encrypted.resize(out_len1 + out_len2);
    return encrypted;
}

void AdvancedStealthReader::SendToVPS(const std::vector<PlayerData>& players) {
    // Convert to JSON
    Json::Value root;
    root["timestamp"] = (Json::UInt64)std::time(nullptr);
    
    Json::Value players_array(Json::arrayValue);
    for (const auto& player : players) {
        Json::Value player_obj;
        player_obj["x"] = player.position.x;
        player_obj["y"] = player.position.y;
        player_obj["z"] = player.position.z;
        player_obj["health"] = player.health;
        player_obj["team"] = player.team;
        player_obj["name"] = player.name;
        player_obj["armor"] = player.armor;
        player_obj["scoped"] = player.is_scoped;
        player_obj["crouching"] = player.is_crouching;
        player_obj["money"] = player.money;
        player_obj["weapon_id"] = player.weapon_id;
        
        players_array.append(player_obj);
    }
    
    root["players"] = players_array;
    
    Json::StreamWriterBuilder writer;
    std::string json_data = Json::writeString(writer, root);
    
    // Encrypt and send
    std::string encrypted = EncryptData(json_data);
    VPSRequest("/api/radar/data", encrypted);
}

std::string AdvancedStealthReader::VPSRequest(const std::string& endpoint, const std::string& data) {
    CURL* curl;
    CURLcode res;
    std::string response;
    
    curl = curl_easy_init();
    if (curl) {
        std::string url = "https://your-vps-domain.com" + endpoint;
        
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_URL, url.c_str());
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_WRITEFUNCTION, WriteCallback);
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_WRITEDATA, &response);
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_USERAGENT, "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36");
        
        if (!data.empty()) {
            curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS, data.c_str());
            curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_POSTFIELDSIZE, data.size());
            
            // Add mimicking headers
            struct curl_slist* headers = NULL;
            headers = curl_slist_append(headers, "Content-Type: application/json");
            headers = curl_slist_append(headers, "Accept: application/json");
            curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, headers);
        }
        
        // SSL verification (disable for testing, enable for production)
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER, 0L);
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST, 0L);
        
        // Timeouts
        curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_TIMEOUT, 10L);
        
        res = curl_easy_perform(curl);
        if (res != CURLE_OK) {
            std::cout << "[-] curl_easy_perform() failed: " << curl_easy_strerror(res) << std::endl;
        }
        
        curl_easy_cleanup(curl);
    }
    
    return response;
}

size_t AdvancedStealthReader::WriteCallback(void* contents, size_t size, size_t nmemb, std::string* response) {
    size_t total_size = size * nmemb;
    response->append((char*)contents, total_size);
    return total_size;
}

// offset_provider.js
const express = require('express');
const axios = require('axios');
const cheerio = require('cheerio');
const NodeCache = require('node-cache');
const crypto = require('crypto');

class OffsetProvider {
    constructor() {
        this.app = express();
        this.cache = new NodeCache({ stdTTL: 300 }); // 5 minute cache
        this.offsetSources = [
            'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/a2x/cs2-dumper/main/output/offsets.json',
            'https://api.github.com/repos/a2x/cs2-dumper/contents/output/offsets.json'
        ];
        
        this.setupRoutes();
        this.startAutoUpdate();
    }
    
    setupRoutes() {
        this.app.get('/api/offsets/latest', async (req, res) => {
            try {
                const offsets = await this.getLatestOffsets();
                res.json({
                    status: 'success',
                    local_player: offsets.client_dll?.dwLocalPlayer?.toString(16),
                    entity_list: offsets.client_dll?.dwEntityList?.toString(16),
                    view_matrix: offsets.client_dll?.dwViewMatrix?.toString(16),
                    radar_info: offsets.client_dll?.dwRadarBase?.toString(16),
                    bone_matrix: offsets.client_dll?.dwBoneMatrix?.toString(16),
                    version: this.getCS2Version(),
                    timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
                });
            } catch (error) {
                res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to fetch offsets' });
            }
        });
        
        this.app.post('/api/offsets/verify', (req, res) => {
            // Verify offset validity
            const { offset, type } = req.body;
            const isValid = this.verifyOffset(offset, type);
            res.json({ valid: isValid });
        });
    }
    
    async getLatestOffsets() {
        // Check cache first
        const cached = this.cache.get('latest_offsets');
        if (cached) return cached;
        
        // Try multiple sources
        for (const source of this.offsetSources) {
            try {
                const offsets = await this.fetchFromSource(source);
                if (offsets) {
                    this.cache.set('latest_offsets', offsets);
                    return offsets;
                }
            } catch (error) {
                console.log(`Failed to fetch from ${source}:`, error.message);
            }
        }
        
        throw new Error('All offset sources failed');
    }
    
    async fetchFromSource(url) {
        const response = await axios.get(url, {
            timeout: 10000,
            headers: {
                'User-Agent': 'Academic-Research-Bot/1.0'
            }
        });
        
        if (url.includes('github.com') && response.data.content) {
            // GitHub API returns base64 encoded content
            const content = Buffer.from(response.data.content, 'base64').toString();
            return JSON.parse(content);
        } else {
            return response.data;
        }
    }
    
    getCS2Version() {
        // This would query Steam API or other sources for current CS2 version
        return '1.38.6.0'; // Example version
    }
    
    verifyOffset(offset, type) {
        // Basic offset validation
        const offsetNum = parseInt(offset, 16);
        
        if (isNaN(offsetNum)) return false;
        
        // Check if offset is within reasonable range
        const minOffset = 0x100000;
        const maxOffset = 0x5000000;
        
        return offsetNum >= minOffset && offsetNum <= maxOffset;
    }
    
    startAutoUpdate() {
        // Update offsets every 5 minutes
        setInterval(async () => {
            try {
                await this.getLatestOffsets();
                console.log('Offsets updated successfully');
            } catch (error) {
                console.log('Offset update failed:', error.message);
            }
        }, 300000);
    }
    
    start(port = 3000) {
        this.app.listen(port, () => {
            console.log(`Offset provider running on port ${port}`);
        });
    }
}

module.exports = OffsetProvider;
